com.github.jukkakarvanen.kafka.streams.test

Class TestInputTopic<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.jukkakarvanen.kafka.streams.test.TestInputTopic<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of the Kafka key
    V - the type of the Kafka value

    public class TestInputTopic<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
    TestInputTopic is used to pipe records to topic in TopologyTestDriver. To use TestInputTopic create new class TopologyTestDriver.createInputTopic(String, Serde, Serde) In actual test code, you can pipe new message values, keys and values or list of KeyValue You need to have own TestInputTopic object for each topic.

    Processing messages

    
     private TestInputTopic<Long, String> inputTopic;
     ...
     inputTopic = testDriver.createInputTopic(INPUT_TOPIC, longSerde, stringSerde);
     ...
     inputTopic.pipeInput("Hello");
    See Also:
    TopologyTestDriver
